but the sample rows in m_orders have created_at as \\"2023-01-05 00:00:00\\". So to extract month, perhaps use DATE_TRUNC or EXTRACT. Let me check standard SQL functions.\\\\n\\\\nIn PostgreSQL, which is common for such problems, EXTRACT(MONTH FROM created_at) would give the month number. But maybe the user expects the month as a string like \\\\\'2023-01\\\\\', but the problem says \\"每月\\", so maybe just the month number. However, the problem says \\"按城市统计每月订单总金额\\", so the result should have city name and month (maybe as year-month) and the sum.\\\\n\\\\nWait, but the problem doesn\\\\\'t specify whether to output the month as a number or a string. But in the query, perhap", "name": "llm_generate_sql", "langgraph_node": "llm_generate_sql", "subagent": null}'}
