agent-worker  | [AuditWorker Debug] Batch count: 10. First item type: <class 'dict'>. Content: {'event_id': '1fba2a8e-cd6b-4cce-b693-92cc77678509', 'schema_version': '1', 'event_type': 'chain_start', 'event_time': '1769365889.3206193', 'run_id': '2df3c428-d6d4-40ed-a3a7-e0bd946abb05', 'session_id': '8d02df79-0abd-4cfb-b6eb-92d103e8be19', 'thread_id': 'f67aa828-3299-457e-90e3-ae41a71357b6', 'span_id': '019bf66c-e128-7300-a80a-b4c609538ec6', 'parent_span_id': '019bf66c-2c3f-70d2-a9bb-5564d43c914d', 'component': 'agent', 'actor_type': 'agent', 'actor_id': 'worker', 'payload_json': '{"inputs_digest": "{\'messages\': [{\'content\': \'按城市和月份统计每月订单总金额，生成SQL查询语句\', \'additional_kwargs\': {}, \'response_metadata\': {}, \'type\': \'human\', \'name\': None, \'id\': None}, {\'content\': \'<think>Okay, let\\\\\'s see. The user wants to get the total order amount per city and month. So first, I need to figure out which tables to join.\\\\n\\\\nLooking at the schema: m_orders has customer_id, which links to m_customers via customer_id. Then m_customers has city_id, which links to m_cities on id. So the chain is m_orders → m_customers → m_cities.\\\\n\\\\nThe goal is to group by city name and month. The created_at is a datetime, so I need to extract the month from that. Maybe using EXTRACT(MONTH FROM created_at) or something like YEAR and MONTH.\\\\n\\\\nWait, the problem says \\"每月订单总金额\\", so per month. So for each city, sum the amount for each month.\\\\n\\\\nSo steps:\\\\n\\\\n1. Join m_orders with m_customers on customer_id.\\\\n2. Join m_customers with m_cities on city_id.\\\\n3. Group by city name and the month extracted from created_at.\\\\n4. Sum the amount.\\\\n\\\\nCheck the columns: m_orders has amount as a string? Wait, in the sample rows, amount is \\"150.00\\", but probably stored as decimal. So need to sum them. But maybe in SQL, if it\\\\\'s a string, need to cast to decimal. But the schema says amount is a column, probably numeric. But maybe the sample shows it as