n name for the date is created_at, not order_date. But the user\\\\\'s example query says \\\\\'order_date\\\\\', but in the schema it\\\\\'s \\\\\'created_at\\\\\'. Wait, the user\\\\\'s instruction says: \\"执行SQL语句：SELECT city, DATE_FORMAT(order_date, \\\\\'%Y-%m\\\\\') AS month, SUM(order_amount) AS total_amount FROM orders GROUP BY city, month\\". Hmm, but the actual column in the schema is \\\\\'created_at\\\\\' and \\\\\'amount\\\\\' (but the sample data shows \\\\\'amount\\\\\' as the order amount). Wait, the sample rows for m_orders have \\\\\'amount\\\\\' as the order amount. So the user might have a typo in the example query, but the actual columns are \\\\\'created_at\\\\\' and \\\\\'amount\\\\\'.\\\\n\\\\nWait, the user\\\\\'s instruction says: \\"查询需求：按城市统计每月订单总金额。请执行SQL语句：SELECT cit"}'}
