agent-worker  | [AuditWorker Debug] Batch count: 10. First item type: <class 'dict'>. Content: {'event_id': 'b00688d5-0b68-414d-a406-c265a5d210ab', 'schema_version': '1', 'event_type': 'chain_end', 'event_time': '1769366229.5850027', 'run_id': '528559b7-8e61-4fb6-959e-58c0f1bfd396', 'session_id': 'b4d57dc5-b9f4-49dd-8f71-ef8b9d9f1841', 'thread_id': 'b4d21d56-e5ca-4ff6-9662-55c114fb35db', 'span_id': '019bf671-e6e6-7a21-8b8d-43f191da6a24', 'parent_span_id': '', 'component': 'chain', 'actor_type': 'agent', 'actor_id': 'worker', 'payload_json': '{"outputs_digest": "{\'generated_sql\': \\"SELECT \\\\n    m_cities.name AS city,\\\\n    DATE_FORMAT(m_orders.created_at, \'%Y-%m\') AS month,\\\\n    SUM(m_orders.amount) AS total_amount\\\\nFROM \\\\n    m_orders\\\\nJOIN \\\\n    m_customers ON m_orders.customer_id = m_customers.id\\\\nJOIN \\\\n    m_cities ON m_customers.city_id = m_cities.id\\\\nWHERE \\\\n    m_orders.status = \'paid\'\\\\nGROUP BY \\\\n    city, month\\\\nORDER BY \\\\n    month;\\", \'messages\': [{\'content\': \'<think>Okay, let\\\\\'s tackle this problem. The user wants to get the total order amount per city and month. Let me check the schema first.\\\\n\\\\nSo, the tables involved are m_cities, m_customers, and m_orders. The m_cities has city names, m_customers links to cities via city_id, and m_orders links to customers via customer_id. The orders table has created_at and amount.\\\\n\\\\nFirst, I need to join m_orders with m_customers to get the city_id for each order. Then join m_cities to get the city name. Wait, but the user wants to group by city, so maybe they want the city name in the result. But the schema says the m_cities table has name. So yes, need to join m_cities to get the city name.\\\\n\\\\nBut the requirement says \\"按城市和月份统计每月订单总金额\\". So the output should have city name and the month (as year-month), and sum of amount.\\\\n\\\\nWait, but the problem says to use DATE_FORMAT on created_at to get year and month. So for each order, format the created_at as \\\\\'%Y-%m\\\\\', then group by that and by city.\\\\n\\\\nSo steps:\\\\n\\\\n1. Join m_orders with m_customers on customer_id to get customer\\\\\'s city_id.\\\\n2. Join m_customers with m_cities on city_id to get city name.\\\\n3. Use DATE_FORMAT(created_at, \\\\\'%Y-%m\\\\\') to get the year-month.\\\\n4. Group by city name and the formatted date, sum the amount.\\\\n5. Order by the formatted date (since it\\\\\'s a string, but maybe better to order by the date part, but the problem says sort by month. However, if the formatted string is like \\\\\'2023-01\\\\\', then ordering by that string will sort correctly. So perhaps order by the formatted year-month.\\\\n\\\\nWait, the user say", "name": "llm_generate_sql", "langgraph_node": "llm_generate_sql", "subagent": null}'}
