acting the month from that.\\\\n\\\\nSo the query should be:\\\\n\\\\nSELECT m_cities.name AS city, EXTRACT(MONTH FROM m_orders.created_at) AS month, SUM(m_orders.amount) AS total_amount\\\\nFROM m_orders\\\\nJOIN m_customers ON m_orders.customer_id = m_customers.id\\\\nJOIN m_cities ON m_customers.city_id = m_cities.id\\\\nGROUP BY city, month\\\\n\\\\nWait, but the user wants the output as a DataFrame. But the SQL query should just generate the data. Also, need to make sure that all non-aggregated columns are in the GROUP BY. Since city is from m_cities.name, and month is extracted from created_at, they should be in the GROUP BY.\\\\n\\\\nWait, the problem ", "name": "LangGraph", "langgraph_node": "tools", "subagent": null}'}
