atabases, the function to extract month might be different. But since the problem doesn\\\\\'t specify the DBMS, but in standard SQL, maybe use EXTRACT(MONTH FROM created_at) or MONTH(created_at). However, the sample data shows created_at as \\\\\'2023-01-05 00:00:00\\\\\', so converting to a date and getting the month.\\\\n\\\\nWait, but in MySQL, you can use MONTH(created_at), but if created_at is a string, maybe need to cast it to datetime first. But the sample data shows the format as \\\\\'YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS\\\\\', so maybe the database stores it as a string, but in SQL, if it\\\\\'s a datetime type, then functions like MONTH() would work. However, the problem says to generate val"}'}
