t SUM(amount) assuming it\\\\\'s numeric.\\\\n\\\\nWait, the schema says amount is a string in the sample rows, but maybe in reality it\\\\\'s a decimal. However, since the user says \\"sum\\", better to convert to numeric. But maybe the database stores it as a decimal. However, the sample shows \\"150.00\\" as a string, but in SQL, if the column is a string, then we need to cast. But perhaps in the actual schema, it\\\\\'s a decimal. Hmm.\\\\n\\\\nBut the problem says to generate valid SQL. So assuming that the amount is stored as a numeric type, so SUM(amount) is okay. But if it\\\\\'s a string, then need to convert. However, the sample data shows \\"150.00\\" as a string, but maybe in the database it\\\\\'s a decimal. Since t", "name": "run_sql", "langgraph_node": "run_sql", "subagent": null}'}
