01-05 00:00:00\\\\\'. So DATE_FORMAT(created_at, \\\\\'%Y-%m\\\\\') would give \\\\\'2023-01\\\\\'.\\\\n\\\\nSo the steps:\\\\n\\\\n1. Select city name from m_cities.\\\\n2. Join m_customers to get city_id to m_cities.\\\\n3. Join m_orders to get customer_id from m_customers.\\\\n4. Filter out orders where status is \\\\\'paid\\\\\'? Wait, the sample rows have status \\\\\'paid\\\\\', but the user didn\\\\\'t specify filtering by status. Wait the problem says \\"按城市和月份统计每月订单总金额\\", so maybe all orders, but the sample data has status \\\\\'paid\\\\\'. Wait, the user didn\\\\\'t mention filtering by status, but in the sample data, the status is \\\\\'paid\\\\\'. However, the problem statement says \\"统计每月订单总金额\\", so maybe all orders, but the schema has stat"}'}
