y_id to m_cities.\\\\n3. Join m_orders to get customer_id from m_customers.\\\\n4. Filter out orders where status is \\\\\'paid\\\\\'? Wait, the sample rows have status \\\\\'paid\\\\\', but the user didn\\\\\'t specify filtering by status. Wait the problem says \\"按城市和月份统计每月订单总金额\\", so maybe all orders, but the sample data has status \\\\\'paid\\\\\'. Wait, the user didn\\\\\'t mention filtering by status, but in the sample data, the status is \\\\\'paid\\\\\'. However, the problem statement says \\"统计每月订单总金额\\", so maybe all orders, but the schema has status column. However, the user didn\\\\\'t specify to filter by status, so maybe include all orders. But the problem says \\"订单总金额\\", so perhaps all orders regardless of status? Hmm, but the sample rows have status", "name": "llm_generate_sql", "langgraph_node": "llm_generate_sql", "subagent": null}'}
