agent-worker  | [AuditWorker Debug] Batch count: 10. First item type: <class 'dict'>. Content: {'event_id': 'a9a710b5-a077-47fb-8736-ba4e54b923fb', 'schema_version': '1', 'event_type': 'run_finished', 'event_time': '1769438954.1541266', 'run_id': '7fc6cd07-9f72-41b3-bc0c-a5e33b59ef4f', 'session_id': '03c82e2f-b1eb-4591-870c-b4940985df74', 'thread_id': '9d4b1fb6-a8ee-4150-9c6f-f788214375a4', 'span_id': '019bfac7-ad4a-7782-90d4-41c61bba1026', 'parent_span_id': '', 'component': 'agent', 'actor_type': 'agent', 'actor_id': 'worker', 'payload_json': '{"outputs_digest": "{\'generated_sql\': \\"SELECT m_cities.name, DATE_FORMAT(m_orders.created_at, \'%Y-%m\') AS month, SUM(m_orders.amount) AS total_amount\\\\nFROM m_orders\\\\nJOIN m_customers ON m_orders.customer_id = m_customers.id\\\\nJOIN m_cities ON m_customers.city_id = m_cities.id\\\\nGROUP BY m_cities.name, DATE_FORMAT(m_orders.created_at, \'%Y-%m\');\\", \'messages\': [{\'content\': \'<think>Okay, let\\\\\'s see. The user wants to get the total order amount per city and month. So first, I need to figure out which tables to join.\\\\n\\\\nLooking at the schema: m_orders has customer_id, which links to m_customers via customer_id. Then m_customers has city_id which links to m_cities. So the path is m_orders -> m_customers -> m_cities.\\\\n\\\\nThe columns needed are city name and the month from order_date. Wait, the order_date is in m_orders as created_at. The user wants to group by city and the month in \\\\\'YYYY-MM\\\\\' format. So DATE_FORMAT(order_date, \\\\\'%Y-%m\\\\\') but in the query, the created_at field is the date.\\\\n\\\\nWait, the sample rows for m_orders show created_at as \\\\\'2023-01-05 00:00:00\\\\\', so the date part is there. So using DATE_FORMAT(created_at, \\\\\'%Y-%m\\\\\') for the month.\\\\n\\\\nBut the city name comes from m_cities. So need to join m_orders with m_customers on customer_id, then m_customers with m_cities on city_id.\\\\n\\\\nSo the steps:\\\\n\\\\n1. Join m_orders to m_customers on customer_id.\\\\n2. Join m_customers to m_cities on city_id.\\\\n3. Group by city name and the formatted month.\\\\n4. Sum the amount.\\\\n\\\\nBut the user says \\"按城市和月份统计订单总金额\\", so total amount per city and month.\\\\n\\\\nWait, the columns to select would be m_cities.name as city, and the formatted month. Then sum amount.\\\\n\\\\nSo the SELECT should be:\\\\n\\\\nSELECT m_cities.name, DATE_FORMAT(m_orders.created_at, \\\\\'%Y-%m\\\\\') AS month, SUM(m_orders.amount) AS total_amount\\\\nFROM m_orders\\\\nJOIN m_customers ON m_orders.customer_id = m_customers.id\\\\nJOIN m_cities ON m_customers.city_id = m_cities.id\\\\nGROUP BY m_cities.name, DATE_FORMAT(m_orders.created_at, \\\\\'%Y-%m\\\\\')\\\\n\\\\nWait, but the"}'}
