y as the column from m_cities.name. So the SELECT should include city from m_cities. But the schema says m_cities has name as the city name. So we need to select m_cities.name as city.\\\\n\\\\nWait the user\'s required query says SELECT city, DATE_FORMAT(order_date, \'%Y-%m\')... but the table has created_at. So in the actual SQL, it\'s created_at. So the column is created_at, not order_date. So the DATE_FORMAT should be on created_at.\\\\n\\\\nSo the steps:\\\\n\\\\n1. Join orders with m_customers on orders.customer_id = m_customers.id\\\\n2. Join m_customers with m_cities on m_customers.city_id = m_cities.id\\\\n3. Select m_cities.name as city\\\\n4. Format created_at to", "name": "llm_generate_sql", "langgraph_node": "llm_generate_sql", "subagent": null}'}
