m the amount.\\\\n\\\\nWait, the user says \\"每月订单总金额\\", so total per city per month.\\\\n\\\\nCheck the columns: m_orders.amount is a string? Wait, sample data shows \\"amount\\": \\"150.00\\", but maybe it\\\\\'s stored as a string. But in SQL, we need to sum it. So maybe cast to decimal or float. But the problem says to generate valid SQL. Maybe the database stores it as a numeric type, but the sample shows string. Hmm. But the problem says to generate SQL, so perhaps the amount is numeric. So SUM(amount) should work.\\\\n\\\\nWait, the sample data shows \\"amount\\": \\"150.00\\", but maybe in the database it\\\\\'s stor", "name": null, "langgraph_node": null, "subagent": null}'}
